args:
A supposed Wyrmclan leader arrives at the
Halidom claiming to bring good fortune, but is
actually a disguised attendant named Chitose.
The real leader—Mitsuhide—is pursuing Ebisu,
who stole all the New Year's gifts. After learning
this, the prince and his friends decide to help.
GUYS! IT'S ALMOST NEW YEAR'S, GUYS!\nARE YOU PUMPED OR WHAT?!
The ceremonial outfits are all ready.
I ain't eaten in a day and a half just to\nmake sure I got room for the feast!
Exactly how much are you planning\nto eat this year, Ranzal?
Well, there certainly doesn't seem\nto be any shortage of enthusiasm.
How could we NOT be excited?\nLast year's shindig was a total blast!
We got presents, we had all sorts of fun,\nand there was good fortune aplenty!
I believe an emissary from Hinomoto is\ncoming here to bring more ＂good fortune＂\nour way this year, yes?
That's right—and I can't wait to see\nwhat they have in store for us.
Excuse me, Your Majesty, but an emissary\nof Hinomoto has arrived at the gates.
Dudes, I can't WAIT to see who this year's\nemissary is! It's gotta be a leader of one\nof the Twelve Wyrmclans, yeah?
Of course! After all, delivering good\nfortune is one of their sacred duties.
Actually, Ieyasu sent me a letter saying\nwe'd be visited by a young woman who's\nhead of the Mouse Clan.
Ah, and what a refined young woman\nshe must be to have such a position!

As the people of Hinomoto select their
shogun from the Wyrmclan leaders,
she will likely be serious, solemn,
and VERY capable.
The emissary is here, Your Majesty.

Heeeeey, everybody! May I present ME,
the cutest Wyrmclan leader EEEVER!
Yep. Biiig ol' Wyrmclan leader. That's me.
No more questions, please!
If you are attempting to sell us something,\nwe are not interested.
We are quite happy with the Ilian Church,\nif conversion is your purpose here.
The heck's goin' on here? I've never seen\nsuch a collection of grumpy gusses.\nCome oooon! Welcome me, already!
Er, y-yes, of course. Please forgive us.\nIt's just that we were expecting someone\nwith a little more...um...gravitas?
If this is ＂serious, solemn, and capable,＂\nI'd sure hate to see dizzy and fun.
Quiet, you dolt! You can't talk to big,\ndumb, important big shots like that!\nBelieve it or not, she's a big deal!
Pretty sure that's ruder than\nanything I just said.
Er, right. Sorry about... Well, all of this.\nAnyway, I'm {player_name}.
You're from the Twelve Wyrmclans, yes?\nAnd you've come in order to bring\ngood fortune to this country?
You're darn tootin' I am—and I'm gonna\nmake you guys so lucky that you have\nfortune falling out of your BUTTS!
That is...quite the image. Er, but have\nyou truly come here all alone?\nWhere are your attendants?

Don't need any! I'm more than enough.
Wanna see my muscles? Maybe buy two
tickets to the ol' trebuchet show? C'mon,
lemme tear off this outfit and show ya!
What on EARTH is happening here?
Hey, speaking of muscles and...whatever,\nwhere's your luggage?
Threw it all away! Who needs bags when\nI'm just gonna tear my clothes off anyway?
Never met someone what hated clothes\nthis much. Still, guess we oughta chat\nabout the fortune yer bringin', yeah?
Well, you're looking at it!\nBehold the blessing of my beauty!
Er, Cleo, I think Her Majesty here needs\nmedical treatment—mainly in the noodle.
No, stop! Don't make me disrobe!\nThose hospital gowns leave nothing\nto the imagination!
Please stop trying to undress\nand acting like it was our idea!
You could not be less like the wise Ieyasu\nwho came last year. Are you truly from\none of the Twelve Wyrmclans?
Aw, snot. I KNEW I'd never be able\nto pull this off.
Fiiine, I'll confess everything.\nI don't lead one of the Twelve Wyrmclans.
Well, that's actually something of a relief.
I mean, sure, I COULD lead one of 'em,\nbut I sorta lack culture and...you know.\nComportment and junk.
Anyway, got anything to eat around here?\nAll this lying makes a boy hungry!
Sorry, wait. Back up.\nYou're a boy?
Yeaaah, you've probably never seen\na boy as cute as me before, huh?
But you can't just go around assuming\nthat anyone cute is automatically female.\nGet with the times, man. Sheesh.
There's nothing wrong with boys being\ncompletely adorbs if they want.
All right, you're a boy. That's fine.\nBut it's also not the most important\nissue we need to deal with here.
If you're not the Wyrmclan leader,\nwho ARE you?
I'm an attendant of Mitsuhide—who\nactually IS one of the Wyrmclan leaders.
She'd intended to come here,\nbut things sorta went sideways.
Mitsuhide, eh? Bit of an odd name.
Mitsuhide is a hereditary name. Be you\nmale or female, the clan leader always\ninherits that name.

It's an old tradition that... Well, there's
some difficult circumstances rolled up
in it. But I'll let Mitsuhide fill you in on
the deets when you meet her.
Aaaanyway, long story significantly longer,\nshe and I were on our way to your castle\nwhen we got ambushed.
And that stupid kitty got away with ALL the\nstuff we brought to bring you good fortune!
Sorry. Your possessions were\nstolen by a...kitty?
Yeah! A dragon kitty named Ebisu!
He got away with everything—cooking\ningredients, decorations, AND gifts!
Ooo-kay. But why did you pretend to\nbe your master and come here instead\nof just chasing down the...kitty dragon?
Because having your good fortune stolen\nis considered totally disgraceful in\nHinomoto. We're talking MAJOR dishonor.

That's why we came up with this plan!
Mitsuhide and the others were supposed
to retrieve the goods while I bought
time with my masterful impersonation.
So this was all one big trick?

Pro tip, bud: If you wanna trick someone,
don't admit that you aren't who you're
pretending to be, like, 15 seconds
into the ruse.
Yeah, but no harm done, right?\nWe're all cool here?
Oh, we're cool. But if ya came here to\nbuy time, I'd say ya ran out a while ago.
Actually, you're right—Mitsuhide and the\nrest of the group absolutely should have\nshown up by now.
That's why I changed the plan.\nIt's called...IMPROVISING! Zing!
I figured it would be a whole lot faster to\njust spit out the truth to you guys and see\nif I could get your help. Smart, no?
Yeah! Will you hear my humble plea,\nO Great {player_name}?
Only if you never refer to me as\n＂O Great {player_name}＂ again.
Then please save Mitsuhide and recover\nthe good fortune stolen by Ebisu!
Pleeeease? With a cherry on top?
Is aught amiss, Your Majesty?\nYou seem distracted.
Has the sight of that adorable Chitose\nsent your head a'spinning?
No, I just... Uhhh... Right then!\nWe'd better go save Mitsuhide's group!
Your Majesty, might we discuss this\nfor a moment? ...Your Majesty!
Aw, maaan! This celebration both sucks\nAND blows. I just want it to be super fun\nthe way it was last year.
If we wanna have another fun New Year's,\nwe gotta recover that fortune.
See? Ol' muscles here gets it.\nNow come on, everyone! To meeeee!
Hey! You don't getta say that!
